# Component Folder Structure

- Each component must be in its own folder named with the component name.
- The component entry file must be `index.tsx`.
- Co-locate related files inside the same component folder.

# Required/Preferred Files

- `index.tsx` -> component implementation and exported component.
- `styles.ts` or `styles.css` -> component styles.
- `consts.ts` -> static labels, arrays, config, and constants.
- `utils.ts` -> component-specific pure helper functions.
- `types.ts` -> shared types/interfaces when the component grows.

# Usage Rules

- Avoid placing component-specific constants or utils in unrelated global files.
- Keep imports relative and local-first (component folder files first, then shared modules).
- If a helper/style/const is reused by multiple components, move it to a shared module.

# Example

```text
src/components/Navbar/
  index.tsx
  styles.ts
  consts.ts
  utils.ts
  types.ts
```
